Error: Error: "Could Not Create The Java Virtual Machine"

Solution: 1. Open the Minecraft launcher and click on the "Launch Options" tab.
2. Select the profile that is giving you the error.
3. In the "JVM Arguments" box, find the line that starts with "-Xmx" or "-Xms" and increase the value.
4. This line sets the maximum and initial size of the Java Virtual Machine. Try increasing the value by 256 MB increments until the error
